07/20/26

When you start a new life,
know that your past
will not die easy.

Try as you might
to replace your habits
and imprecise memories,
your mind will be branded
by the shallowest currents
of yesteryear's strifes.

Like Kylo Ren,
you must selfishly strike
and betray the bellies
of your time-torn captors,
your hardships, your woes,
your mistakes and regrets,
your self-inflicted wounds,
and the loves you still long for.

And when I return, as I inevitably will,
when the noon sun reclines towards the South
and the sidewalks teem with ice,
I will be reborn, like a satin phoenix
to my friends, family, and colleagues;
to my city streets and beaches;
to my mysteries and vices all.

And when I do,
they will know me by a different name --
a new name, the name thrust upon me
on my way out the door --
a name I have so callously chosen to accept.

They will call me Mr. Delaware.